3.00	Klaus_Wagner	Klaus Wagner (mathematician)	Klaus Wagner (March 31, 1910 – February 6, 2000) was a German mathematician. He studied topology at the University of Cologne under the supervision of Karl Dörge, who had been a student of Issai Schur. Wagner received his Ph.D. in 1937, and taught at Cologne for many years himself. In 1970, he moved to the University of Duisburg, where he remained until his retirement in 1978.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Wagner_and_Harary.jpg/240px-Wagner_and_Harary.jpg
